…Vows To Secure Nigeria, Bring Enduring Peace ABUJA – The 22nd indigenous Acting Inspector General of Police (IGP), Kayode Egbetokun who took over the leadership of the Nigeria Police Force, today has vowed to secure Nigeria and bring enduring peace to our nation. He also promised to establish a robust internal system to investigate the misconduct of police personnel, while calling on the citizens to join hands with him in delivering on his promises. Egbetokun, a doctorate degree holder took over from the immediate past IGP Usman Alkali Baba, who was appointed by President Muhammadu Buhari in 2021. Details soon….